The paper discusses research in human-centered AI, specifically focusing on machine learning models that can explain their predictions and allow users to tune the model in response to the explanations. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper applies the framework to a neural recommender system for scientific papers, indicating that it could also fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
